00:21:14,739 --> 00:21:18,223
letter spacing. I see some smiles. So, that's good.

339
00:21:18,243 --> 00:21:19,043
I'm a kerning fan.

340
00:21:21,926 --> 00:21:25,388
So, kerning is the adjustment between two letters.

341
00:21:25,888 --> 00:21:26,308
Just two.

342
00:21:26,328 --> 00:21:28,489
And that's why they call it a kerning pair.

343
00:21:30,170 --> 00:21:32,391
You can have positive or negative kerning values.

344
00:21:32,991 --> 00:21:36,853
And these values, as they're added by a type designer like myself,

345
00:21:36,933 --> 00:21:38,574
are stored inside the font file.

346
00:21:40,115 --> 00:21:41,996
Some apps like Photoshop or Illustrator

347
00:21:42,016 --> 00:21:46,018
would allow you to manually override those default kerning values.

348
00:21:47,867 --> 00:21:53,330
Tracking, on the other hand, is the adjustment between all of the letters, positive or negative

349
00:21:53,410 --> 00:21:54,031
in the same way.

350
00:21:54,591 --> 00:21:59,774
The font has a default spacing built in at zero here, and the app that's using the font

351
